conbody.p: Create a ray (semi-infinite line) from a combination of options including point, direction and angle.

section.title: Methods to begin a ray
section.p: There are six methods to begin creating a ray:
You can continue adding unlimited rays until you press Enter to end the command.

dlentry.dd: Begin creating a ray by specifying the starting point of the ray then:
Specify the direction of the ray from the starting point.
Begin creating a ray horizontal to the x-axis then:
Specify the starting point of the ray.
Begin creating a ray parallel to the y-axis then:
Specify the starting point of the ray.
Begin creating a ray based on an angle then:
Specify the angle of the ray.
Additional option: [Reference]
Specify the starting point of the ray.
Begin creating a ray which bisects the angle between two imaginary lines then:
Specify the start point of the ray.
Additional option: [Entity]
Specify a point to define the first imaginary line. The vertex is used as the other point.
Specify a point to define the second imaginary line. The vertex is used as the other point.
Begin creating a ray parallel to a line or polyline segment then:

dlentry.dt: Set offset distance for parallel infinite ray
dlentry.dd: Specify the offset distance for the ray.
Additional option: [Through point]

dlentry.dt: Select entity for parallel infinite ray
dlentry.dd: Select a line or polyline segment from which to offset the ray.
Specify the side on which to place the ray. The ray’s start point is parallel to the line’s start point.

section.title: Options within the RAY command
section.p: After you begin creating a ray, the following options may be available:

dlentry.dd: Select an entity to use a reference angle then:

dd.p: Specify the angle to place the ray relative to the selected entity.

dlentry.dd: Specify the starting point of the ray.
The Location prompt repeats so that you can draw more angled rays with different starting points. Press Enter to end the command.
Select a line, arc, a polyline segment to bisect then:
Specify the side on which to place the ray.

When you select a line or polyline segment, the command draws the xline perpendicular to the segment’s midpoint. When you select an arc or polyarc, the command draws the xline perpenduclar to the arc’s center and midpoint.
This command works with splined polylines, but not with splined entities.
Specify a point through which to draw the ray.

dlentry.dt: Select entity for parallel infinite ray
dlentry.dd: Specify the entity to offset with the ray.
Specify the point through which to draw the ray. This point is the ray’s start point.
